NAME		sort -- sort a file
.sp
.ti 0
SYNOPSIS	sort____ input output
.sp
.ti 0
DESCRIPTION	sort____
will sort the input file and write the
sorted file on the output file.
The sort is line-by-line in increasing ASCII collating sequence.

Space required is 6*number-of-lines in bytes.
.sp
.ti 0
FILES		/tmp/stm?
.sp
.ti 0
SEE ALSO	--
.sp
.ti 0
DIAGNOSTICS	--
.sp
.ti 0
BUGS		Sort
does not put a maximum on the size of file that it sorts.
Thus a bus error will occur if
too large an input file is supplied.
.sp
The input is copied to a temporary file.
Thus the maximum file that can be sorted
is the maximum non-special file (currently 64K bytes.)
.sp
.in 0
